oiimg.com/photo/msid-132607522,imgsize-68084.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[North Carolina to hold first Elk hunt In 2027 after rebuilding herd over 25 years]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132606207.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[North Carolina will allow its first elk hunt in 2027, 25 years after reintroducing the species. Only two hunting permits will be issued through an auction and raffle, with proceeds supporting elk conservation. Wildlife officials say the population is now sustainable, while some local residents remain divided over whether hunting should begin.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/north-carolina-spent-25-years-rebuilding-an-elk-population-that-had-disappeared-from-the-state-in-2027-it-will-allow-its-first-limited-hunt-with-just-two-permits/articleshow/132606207.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/north-carolina-spent-25-years-rebuilding-an-elk-population-that-had-disappeared-from-the-state-in-2027-it-will-allow-its-first-limited-hunt-with-just-two-permits/articleshow/132606207.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T19:30:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132607023,imgsize-80650.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Google co-founder Sergey Brin turned his $450 million superyacht into a floating headquarters with an entire deck dedicated to work]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132606960.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/google-co-founder-sergey-brin-turned-his-450-million-superyacht-into-a-floating-headquarters-with-an-entire-deck-dedicated-to-work/articleshow/132606960.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/google-co-founder-sergey-brin-turned-his-450-million-superyacht-into-a-floating-headquarters-with-an-entire-deck-dedicated-to-work/articleshow/132606960.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T18:57:04+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132607046,imgsize-1501191.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Thailand is placing seagrass inside 3D-printed shelters because animals destroy it before it grows]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132604385.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/thailand-is-placing-young-seagrass-inside-3d-printed-shelters-because-waves-and-hungry-animals-destroy-it-before-it-can-grow/articleshow/132604385.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/thailand-is-placing-young-seagrass-inside-3d-printed-shelters-because-waves-and-hungry-animals-destroy-it-before-it-can-grow/articleshow/132604385.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T18:49:51+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132606670,imgsize-97652.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[King Charles III emerges from Tardis in ‘Doctor Who’ moment at Commonwealth Games 2026 opening]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132606220.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/king-charles-iii-emerges-from-tardis-in-doctor-who-moment-at-commonwealth-games-2026-opening/articleshow/132606220.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/king-charles-iii-emerges-from-tardis-in-doctor-who-moment-at-commonwealth-games-2026-opening/articleshow/132606220.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T18:46:42+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132606882,imgsize-821471.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[How four Moose released in 1904 ended up reshaping Newfoundland's forests forever]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132604580.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A century after just four moose were released in Newfoundland to attract hunters, the introduced animals transformed the island's forests and wildlife management. Their population grew to nearly 200,000 before habitat damage triggered declines. A new management plan explains how science is now helping keep moose numbers in balance with forests, public safety and long-term ecosystem health.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/in-1904-newfoundland-released-four-moose-to-attract-hunters-their-population-later-reached-200000-and-began-reshaping-the-islands-forests/articleshow/132604580.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/in-1904-newfoundland-released-four-moose-to-attract-hunters-their-population-later-reached-200000-and-began-reshaping-the-islands-forests/articleshow/132604580.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T18:44:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132606009,imgsize-240600.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[No good news for Indian B1/B2 visa applicants yet: $750 fast visa appointment pilot program starts in Mexico]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132605933.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/no-good-news-for-indian-b1/b2-visa-applicants-yet-750-fast-visa-appointment-pilot-program-starts-in-mexico/articleshow/132605933.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/no-good-news-for-indian-b1/b2-visa-applicants-yet-750-fast-visa-appointment-pilot-program-starts-in-mexico/articleshow/132605933.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T18:09:40+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132605997,imgsize-168080.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[1,800-year-old Roman camp linked to Marcus Aurelius found in Slovakia]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132603084.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Archaeologists have discovered an approximately 1,800-year-old Roman military camp in southwestern Slovakia that may have been used by Emperor Marcus Aurelius' army during the Marcomannic Wars. The site contains skeletons believed to be Roman soldiers buried in shallow graves, ditches and wells, along with weapons, armour, coins and military sandals. Researchers say the rare discovery could provide new insights into Roman military campaigns, although years of scientific analysis are needed to answer key questions about the soldiers' deaths and the camp's abandonment.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/1800-year-old-roman-camp-linked-to-marcus-aurelius-found-in-slovakia-possible-soldiers-lay-in-pits-and-wells-with-armour-left-behind/articleshow/132603084.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/1800-year-old-roman-camp-linked-to-marcus-aurelius-found-in-slovakia-possible-soldiers-lay-in-pits-and-wells-with-armour-left-behind/articleshow/132603084.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T17:29:32+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132603537,imgsize-148192.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Quote of the day by Erling Haaland: 'I can improve everything. If you think I'm good at one thing, I can always get better']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132604698.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/quote-of-the-day-by-erling-haaland-i-can-improve-everything-if-you-think-im-good-at-one-thing-i-can-always-get-better/articleshow/132604698.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/quote-of-the-day-by-erling-haaland-i-can-improve-everything-if-you-think-im-good-at-one-thing-i-can-always-get-better/articleshow/132604698.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T17:21:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132604746,imgsize-102258.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Setback for Hindu Americans: California court strikes down state’s Diwali holiday law]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132603847.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/setback-for-hindu-americans-california-court-strikes-down-states-diwali-holiday-law/articleshow/132603847.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/setback-for-hindu-americans-california-court-strikes-down-states-diwali-holiday-law/articleshow/132603847.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T17:27:54+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132604896,imgsize-676898.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Inside Tuvalu: This tiny island nation has one airline, and a threatened future]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132604297.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/inside-tuvalu-this-tiny-island-nation-has-just-one-airline-almost-no-tourists-and-a-future-threatened-by-rising-seas/articleshow/132604297.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/inside-tuvalu-this-tiny-island-nation-has-just-one-airline-almost-no-tourists-and-a-future-threatened-by-rising-seas/articleshow/132604297.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T17:10:39+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132604297,imgsize-1392855.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Bangladesh President Mohammad Shahabuddin resigns ahead of Sheikh Hasina's planned return, reports of rift with govt]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132603622.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/bangladesh-president-mohammad-shahabuddin-resigns-ahead-of-sheikh-hasinas-planned-return-reports-of-rift-with-govt/articleshow/132603622.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/bangladesh-president-mohammad-shahabuddin-resigns-ahead-of-sheikh-hasinas-planned-return-reports-of-rift-with-govt/articleshow/132603622.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T16:41:18+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132603718,imgsize-86645.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Quote of the day by John Stuart Mill: 'A person may cause evil to others not only by his actions but by his inaction, and in either case he is justly accountable to them for the injury']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132604824.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Philosopher John Stuart Mill emphasized the importance of accountability for both actions and inaction. He argued that choosing not to intervene in situations that could prevent harm carries its own set of responsibilities. This principle is particularly relevant in instances of bullying, corruption, or injustice, where those with authority must acknowledge their complicity. Mill's insightful quote challenges us to embrace moral responsibility and reflect on the repercussions of our silence.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/quote-of-the-day-by-john-stuart-mill-a-person-may-cause-evil-to-others-not-only-by-his-actions-but-by-his-inaction-and-in-either-case-he-is-justly-accountable-to-them-for-the-injury/articleshow/132604824.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/quote-of-the-day-by-john-stuart-mill-a-person-may-cause-evil-to-others-not-only-by-his-actions-but-by-his-inaction-and-in-either-case-he-is-justly-accountable-to-them-for-the-injury/articleshow/132604824.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T17:31:50+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132604965,imgsize-51126.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[500-year-old place with 200 skeletons buried beneath it: Construction workers uncover it]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132603160.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/construction-workers-in-ghent-uncover-a-500-year-old-neighbourhood-with-200-skeletons-buried-beneath-it/articleshow/132603160.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/construction-workers-in-ghent-uncover-a-500-year-old-neighbourhood-with-200-skeletons-buried-beneath-it/articleshow/132603160.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T16:22:32+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132603160,imgsize-2272310.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Quote of the day by Oprah Winfrey: 'If you look at what you have in life, you'll always have more. If you look at what you don't have in life, you'll never have enough']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132605084.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Oprah Winfrey emphasizes the profound impact of gratitude on our fulfillment in life. By centering our attention on what we possess, we cultivate a sense of satisfaction and contentment. In stark contrast, fixating on what's lacking breeds an endless cycle of dissatisfaction. In a world where constant comparison is prevalent, embracing our current situation while striving for future goals nurtures a healthier mindset.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/quote-of-the-day-by-oprah-winfrey-if-you-look-at-what-you-have-in-life-youll-always-have-more-if-you-look-at-what-you-dont-have-in-life-youll-never-have-enough/articleshow/132605084.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/quote-of-the-day-by-oprah-winfrey-if-you-look-at-what-you-have-in-life-youll-always-have-more-if-you-look-at-what-you-dont-have-in-life-youll-never-have-enough/articleshow/132605084.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T17:45:30+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132605313,imgsize-165062.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['My partner is half-Indian': Elon Musk rejects racism allegations, says his son's name honours Indian scientist Subrahmanyan Chandrasekhar]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132603344.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/my-partner-is-half-indian-elon-musk-rejects-racism-allegations-says-his-sons-name-honours-indian-scientist-subrahmanyan-chandrasekhar/articleshow/132603344.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/my-partner-is-half-indian-elon-musk-rejects-racism-allegations-says-his-sons-name-honours-indian-scientist-subrahmanyan-chandrasekhar/articleshow/132603344.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T16:38:28+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132603408,imgsize-48908.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Oregon proposes fees of up to nearly $5 million for undersea cables using its coastal seabed, with payments benefiting public schools]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132603591.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Oregon is introducing new fees for undersea cable installations near its coast.  These charges will generate revenue for the state's public K-12 schools.  Existing fees were established about twenty-five years ago and were much lower.  The new rates aim to attract tech investment while ensuring compensation.  This update follows a 2020 incident involving a cable construction project.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/the-undersea-internet-cables-connecting-continents-could-soon-help-fund-public-schools-as-oregon-proposes-charging-millions-in-new-fees-to-tech-companies/articleshow/132603591.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/the-undersea-internet-cables-connecting-continents-could-soon-help-fund-public-schools-as-oregon-proposes-charging-millions-in-new-fees-to-tech-companies/articleshow/132603591.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T16:37:26+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132603618,imgsize-242122.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Resilient shelter dog Duke finds forever home after heartbreaking journey]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132603131.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Duke, a shelter dog, faced multiple losses including his home and bonded sister. He endured two failed adoptions within a single day at the shelter. A volunteer shared Duke's story online, which reached a woman nine hours away. This woman instantly decided to adopt Duke, bringing him to his new home. Duke now lives a happy life with a family committed to him.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/us-and-world/shelter-dog-duke-lost-his-home-was-separated-from-his-bonded-sister-and-endured-two-failed-adoptions-one-video-finally-found-him-a-family-nine-hours-away/articleshow/132603131.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/us-and-world/shelter-dog-duke-lost-his-home-was-separated-from-his-bonded-sister-and-endured-two-failed-adoptions-one-video-finally-found-him-a-family-nine-hours-away/articleshow/132603131.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T16:18:06+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132603148,imgsize-110052.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Canada recalls Briine Pacific Tide sparkling water in Alberta after 355ml cans begin bulging]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132600190.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[The Government of Canada has recalled Briine Pacific Tide Sparkling Spring Waterin Alberta after some355 ml canswere found to be bulging. The recall has been issued due tonon-harmful microbial contamination (quality or spoilage). Consumers and retailers have been advised not to use, sell, serve or distribute the affected product and to check thetwo affected best-before codes: 01AL2028 and 02AL2028.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/canada-recalls-briine-pacific-tide-sparkling-water-in-alberta-after-355ml-cans-begin-bulging-check-two-affected-codes/articleshow/132600190.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/canada-recalls-briine-pacific-tide-sparkling-water-in-alberta-after-355ml-cans-begin-bulging-check-two-affected-codes/articleshow/132600190.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T16:06:40+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132602264,imgsize-85384.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Dozens of Indian-origin men among 21 charged in $139m